# GPRTool -- Project Brief

## What this is
GPRTool is a browser-based CAD PWA for calculating Green Plot Ratio (GPR), a greenery metric invented by Boon Ong (Ong 2003, 460+ citations). It renders a 3D scene via Three.js with two viewports (2D plan + 3D perspective), lets users import building geometry, place plants from an LAI database, and compute GPR scores. Stack: vanilla HTML/CSS/JS + Three.js, no npm, no frameworks. Deployed on Vercel via GitHub. Use Microsoft Edge for development -- Chrome has rendering issues.

## Current focus
Modular extraction of index.html into discrete JS files under app/js/ (target: index.html as ~50-line shell). North-point compass bugs fixed (April 2026). Next priorities: LAI database merge (Singapore field data + ORNL/TRY), plant placement refinement, and Import by Address (Landgate SLIP API).

## Key constraints
- Vanilla JS only -- no TypeScript, no Node.js APIs, no npm packages in app/
- LAI database (LAI_categorised.csv) is core IP -- never send to external APIs
- Touch it, extract it -- any index.html section opened must be extracted to app/js/ in the same PR
- Third-party libs live in app/js/lib/ -- never edit these files
- Icons always inline SVG, never <img> with PNG
- Two coordinate systems must stay strictly separate: Global (Three.js world, -Z = True North) and Design (user-set via designNorthAngle)
- Always propose + get approval before writing any file

## Known issues
- LAI database: Singapore field data (37 species) merge pending -- duplicates in Singapore CSV unresolved
- index.html still contains substantial inline code awaiting extraction

